Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.38,0:05:30.03,JoJo-top,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,J-Jotaro?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.03,0:05:30.72,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.08,0:05:34.00,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Jotaro! Why are you sitting down?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.00,0:05:37.35,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,I'll defeat him! I'm next!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.81,0:05:44.08,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,Old man, have you played any one of \Nthese games more than Kakyoin has?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.67,0:05:48.18,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,Stay out of this, old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.53,0:05:51.15,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't like playing cards or hanafuda.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.69,0:05:55.29,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,Next is baseball.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.66,0:05:59.46,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to play this baseball game with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.16,0:06:03.46,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,I'll wager my soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.46,0:06:06.97,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Good. And I shall wager Kakyoin's.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.47,0:06:14.14,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,I have retrieved my Stand \NAtum's arm from your arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.84,0:06:17.49,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I have Kakyoin's soul,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.49,0:06:21.11,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,there's no point in holding \Non to your arm anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.57,0:06:23.77,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,It would put my Stand at a disadvantage
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.77,0:06:27.53,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,to fight you with only one arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.98,0:06:32.07,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Your Star Platinum's movements are \Nextremely fast and super precise.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.06,0:06:37.27,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,But to think that you'd pick this baseball game...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.36,0:06:42.50,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,This is the game I'm best at.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.50,0:06:49.03,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,D'Arby! As soon as you lose \Nto Jotaro, I will finish you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.03,0:06:50.64,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Remember that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.74,0:06:57.71,JoJo-Kaboom,sfx,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(183,419)}Kaboom
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.74,0:06:58.23,JoJo-announcertop,game,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! That's A Baseball!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.33,0:07:03.89,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,There is no trickery in this game.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.89,0:07:05.15,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,I've confirmed that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.50,0:07:09.01,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,First, please pick your team.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.22,0:07:12.32,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,The Jaguars.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.98,0:07:14.43,JoJo-announcer,game,0000,0000,0000,,Jaguars!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.65,0:07:16.95,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.95,0:07:20.18,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,So you've chosen a team with a strong offense.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.72,0:07:23.28,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Two of your players have\Nbatting averages over .400.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.28,0:07:26.55,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Then I shall choose the Red Dragons.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.55,0:07:28.57,JoJo-announcer,game,0000,0000,0000,,Red Dragons!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.56,0:07:32.34,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Would you like to bat first \Nor second? Take your pick.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.72,0:07:34.68,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,First.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.68,0:07:38.27,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Very well. The Jaguars are up first.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.50,0:07:44.08,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,You can draw your own characters\Nto input as the players.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.99,0:07:47.67,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,This is Star Platinum.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.77,0:07:54.50,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Input. Now, let us play ball!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.52,0:08:00.66,JoJo-announcer,game,0000,0000,0000,,Jaguars versus Red Dragons.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.66,0:08:02.10,JoJo-announcer,ump,0000,0000,0000,,Play ball!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.03,0:08:09.59,Inning,sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(582,1)}Top of the 1st
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.91,0:08:15.26,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,I've chosen #15 to be my pitcher,\Nsince I was born on January 5th.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.29,0:08:20.11,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Here I go.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.56,0:08:21.98,JoJo-announcer,game,0000,0000,0000,,The pitcher is winding up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.98,0:08:25.07,JoJo-announcer,game,0000,0000,0000,,The first pitch!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.92,0:08:27.94,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.92,0:08:31.07,JoJo-announcer,ump,0000,0000,0000,,Strike!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.64,0:08:37.06,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey, Jotaro. What did you just do?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.06,0:08:41.62,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,You swung the bat before the\Nball even left the pitcher's hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.17,0:08:53.46,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey, Jotaro... Why do you \Nkeep taking practice swings?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.96,0:08:57.68,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me... Could it be that you...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.02,0:09:00.14,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Have you played this baseball game—No,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.14,0:09:03.17,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,have you ever played {\i1}any{\i0} video game before?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.93,0:09:06.17,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Answer me, Jotaro!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.45,0:09:09.52,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever. I know the rules for baseball.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.88,0:09:12.03,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,I'll figure out the controls as I go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.11,0:09:15.32,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.78,0:09:19.13,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,That ridiculous, terribly-timed swing!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.13,0:09:20.86,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,The way you're working the controls...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.86,0:09:23.56,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,This is your first time playing {\i1}any{\i0} game, isn't it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.37,0:09:35.00,JoJo-announcer,ump,0000,0000,0000,,Strike two!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.11,0:09:39.71,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,This time, you swung the bat \Nafter the ball hit the mitt!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.71,0:09:41.06,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a total amateur!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.06,0:09:42.81,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,God damn it, Jotaro!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.81,0:09:45.81,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,You've never played a\Nvideo game before, have you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.35,0:09:48.56,JoJo-announcer,ump,0000,0000,0000,,Strike! Batter out!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.36,0:09:51.35,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Stop messing around, Jotaro!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.35,0:09:53.84,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you putting on that attitude?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.84,0:09:58.68,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,You wagered your own soul! \NYou can't back out now!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.68,0:10:00.00,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,Good grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.00,0:10:02.13,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,You should be supportive at times like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.50,0:10:06.17,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,"It's just the first inning. \NYou've only just started.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.17,0:10:08.05,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,You can do it, Jotaro." Like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.05,0:10:10.04,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,What are you thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.04,0:10:14.34,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Even with your Star Platinum's \Nsuper precise movements,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.34,0:10:19.15,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,did you think you could beat him with\Nno knowledge of video games at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.46,0:10:23.49,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,What are you thinking, Jotaro?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.49,0:10:25.72,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,What on Earth are you thinking?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.31,0:10:28.27,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Jotaro...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.02,0:10:32.29,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Let me warn you that if, on the other hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.29,0:10:34.99,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,this is some plan to trick me \Nby acting like an amateur,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.99,0:10:36.68,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,it's not going to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.67,0:10:40.32,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,No matter the situation,\NI never let down my guard.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.32,0:10:43.30,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Once my opponent has wagered \Nhis soul, even if he is an infant,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.30,0:10:44.95,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,I would give my all to defeat him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.37,0:10:47.31,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,Old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.69,0:10:50.74,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not thinking about anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.43,0:10:52.37,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,Except...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.85,0:10:56.59,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,about breaking that asshole's nose,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.59,0:11:02.26,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,as he sits there so certain that he'll \Nnever lose to anyone in this game.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.70,0:11:07.77,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,I'm only seriously thinking about \Ngetting Kakyoin's soul back.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.74,0:11:11.36,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,You can say what you'd like...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.36,0:11:14.15,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,But it's still the top of the \Nfirst inning with one out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.15,0:11:15.90,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Let us continue the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.28,0:11:18.35,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't forget that if one of us
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.35,0:11:22.76,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,takes an eleven-point lead, \Nthe game will be called.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.00,0:11:29.16,JoJo-announcer,game,0000,0000,0000,,Second batter, #3.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.53,0:11:34.46,JoJo-announcer,ump,0000,0000,0000,,Strike!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.74,0:11:37.05,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Th-This can't be happening!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.05,0:11:39.48,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,This time, the ball was at\Nleast 40 centimeters away
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.48,0:11:41.34,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,from where he swung the bat!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.02,0:11:43.43,JoJo-announcer,ump,0000,0000,0000,,Strike two!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.43,0:11:45.14,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Not even close!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.30,0:11:51.95,JoJo-announcer,ump,0000,0000,0000,,Strike! Batter out!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.74,0:11:55.15,JoJo-internal/narrator,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,It's no use.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.15,0:11:57.91,JoJo-internal/narrator,,0000,0000,0000,,The difference in ability is too obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.91,0:12:00.25,JoJo-internal/narrator,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate, it's as if a tea ceremony club,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.25,0:12:04.45,JoJo-internal/narrator,,0000,0000,0000,,where nobody's ever held a bat,\Ndecided to challenge a championship team.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.81,0:12:06.28,JoJo-internal/narrator,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,It's too pathetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.70,0:12:07.45,JoJo-announcer,ump,0000,0000,0000,,Strike!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.88,0:12:09.42,JoJo-announcer,ump,0000,0000,0000,,Strike two!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.95,0:12:15.78,JoJo-internal/narrator,ter,0000,0000,0000,,It seems he truly is an amateur. He's too weak!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.78,0:12:18.51,JoJo-internal/narrator,ter,0000,0000,0000,,I think I now understand how a judo master feels
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.51,0:12:21.31,JoJo-internal/narrator,,0000,0000,0000,,when he can gauge his opponent's strength simply
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.31,0:12:23.69,JoJo-internal/narrator,,0000,0000,0000,,from how he puts on his gi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.69,0:12:27.60,JoJo-internal/narrator,ter,0000,0000,0000,,When it comes to video games,\NJotaro is indeed an amateur.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.24,0:12:31.73,JoJo-internal/narrator,ter,0000,0000,0000,,But I will never let my guard down.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.20,0:12:35.35,JoJo-internal/narrator,ter,0000,0000,0000,,I've memorized the weaknesses of \Nall the batters in this game.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.98,0:12:38.75,JoJo-internal/narrator,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Next will be a low pitch to the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.17,0:12:43.86,JoJo-internal/narrator,ter,0000,0000,0000,,I'll throw my ultimate screwball and strike \Nout all three without a single run.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.26,0:12:48.03,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Top of the first, two outs, \Ntwo strikes and no balls.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.03,0:12:49.41,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Here comes my next pitch.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.66,0:12:50.66,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.06,0:12:53.91,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,I've pretty much learned how to bat now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.97,0:12:58.38,JoJo-internal/narrator,ter,0000,0000,0000,,What? What did he just say?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.52,0:13:02.69,JoJo-internal/narrator,ter,0000,0000,0000,,"How to bat"? What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.22,0:13:05.68,JoJo-internal/narrator,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Did he just say "pretty much learned"?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.39,0:13:10.26,JoJo-internal/narrator,ter,0000,0000,0000,,What is he talking about? What does he mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.06,0:13:17.23,JoJo-internal/narrator,ter,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.23,0:13:18.75,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Jotaro!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.75,0:13:21.61,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,Good. This game is pretty fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.83,0:13:24.36,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey, don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.36,0:13:27.53,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,It's still going. The ball is still in the air!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.53,0:13:29.57,JoJo-internal/narrator,ter,0000,0000,0000,,What did he say just now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.92,0:13:32.93,JoJo-internal/narrator,ter,0000,0000,0000,,"I've pretty much learned how to bat now."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.93,0:13:35.33,JoJo-internal/narrator,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Learned? Did he just say learned?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.37,0:13:40.24,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's fair!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.24,0:13:43.11,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You're kidding! You're kidding me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.90,0:13:46.28,JoJo-announcer,game,0000,0000,0000,,Home run!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.54,0:13:57.04,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Home run! A home run!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.28,0:14:01.65,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Jotaro! You bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.30,0:14:09.95,JoJo-Eyecatch3,signtop,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(713,1)}Atum
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.97,0:14:09.95,JoJo-Eyecatch2,signbot,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(61,1)}D'Arby Younger
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.95,0:14:12.05,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Jotaro!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.05,0:14:14.18,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,What did you just say?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.18,0:14:18.17,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,"Learned"? "I've pretty much learned \Nhow to bat"? Is that what you said?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.50,0:14:20.46,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,There's no reason for me to say it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.10,0:14:26.10,JoJo-internal/narrator,ter,0000,0000,0000,,He was, without a doubt, a beginner.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.51,0:14:30.34,JoJo-internal/narrator,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Is he saying that he managed to learn\Nthe controls by swinging eight times?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.05,0:14:35.35,JoJo-internal/narrator,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Jotaro Kujo has Star Platinum, \Nwho has the power of super precise movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.77,0:14:37.59,JoJo-internal/narrator,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Now I know exactly why
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.59,0:14:41.02,JoJo-internal/narrator,,0000,0000,0000,,Lord DIO sees him as a problem, \Nand why my brother lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.61,0:14:49.45,JoJo-internal/narrator,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Interesting. This is how my opponents should be.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.11,0:14:52.54,JoJo-internal/narrator,ter,0000,0000,0000,,And you exposed this fearsome
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.54,0:14:57.91,JoJo-internal/narrator,,0000,0000,0000,,characteristic of yours in the top of \Nthe first inning, right after we started...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.91,0:15:01.12,JoJo-internal/narrator,ter,0000,0000,0000,,You'll eventually regret that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.90,0:15:06.38,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Let us continue the game, Jotaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.31,0:15:13.10,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,He did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.39,0:15:15.13,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,It's fair! It's fair!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.13,0:15:17.58,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,He got another home run!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.58,0:15:20.32,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Now it's four to nothing in the top of the first.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.32,0:15:24.52,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like you've got the \Nhang of this game, Jotaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.52,0:15:26.86,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Keep this up! Keep it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.13,0:15:28.98,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, D'Arby.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.98,0:15:32.95,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you don't want to hear this,\Nbut I'll say it as a kindness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.31,0:15:39.12,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,If you return Kakyoin's soul \Nright now and take us to DIO,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.82,0:15:39.41,JoJo-Menacing,sfx,0000,0000,0000,,Menacing
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.12,0:15:41.80,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,we'll spare your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.80,0:15:51.90,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,My brother was a master at gambling,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.90,0:15:54.08,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,and a master at cheating.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.49,0:16:05.02,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Yet he never said to me, "Brother, \Nwhy don't we play a game of poker?"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.02,0:16:06.44,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Not even once.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.25,0:16:08.85,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know why that is?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.73,0:16:16.36,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,When I was fifteen, \Nmy brother hit on my girlfriend.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.36,0:16:19.72,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,I beat the shit out of him, \Neven though he was ten years older.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.72,0:16:23.22,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,I broke his ribs and kicked him \Nuntil he vomited blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.22,0:16:26.46,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,To that, all my brother\Nhad to say was, "I'm sorry."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.06,0:16:28.62,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know why?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.98,0:16:30.92,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,What are you getting at, you bastard?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.17,0:16:36.74,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,My brother knew ever since we were children \Nthat he had no way of beating me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.74,0:16:39.43,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,He knew there was a reason he couldn't win.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.99,0:16:46.06,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,And now, it appears as if Jotaro is getting \Nexcited and really taking off with this game.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.06,0:16:50.68,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,However, he's uncertain,\Njust like my brother was as a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.88,0:16:53.87,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,He's uncertain about my abilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.87,0:16:57.69,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,"Nah, it couldn't be. Or wait, maybe..."\NThat's what he's been thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.69,0:16:59.13,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Jotaro?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.13,0:17:00.95,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.39,0:17:07.97,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,I'm changing pitchers! I'll switch #15 for #77.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.46,0:17:07.96,Columns,sign,0000,0000,0000,,#                Name             G W L H S ERA
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.46,0:17:07.96,Rows,sign,0000,0000,0000,,15) Starting Pitcher \N55) Relief Pitcher \N77) Closer \N90) Relief Pitcher\N84) Starting Pitcher
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.46,0:17:07.96,Upper Right,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Number\NPosition\N\NGames \NWins\NLosses\NH \NS  \NERA
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.37,0:17:13.97,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,#77 is a fastball pitcher, whose fastest pitch clocks in at 165 kilometers per hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.46,0:17:13.96,Number,sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(484,1)}Number
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.46,0:17:13.96,Rows 2,sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(484,1)}Right-handed \NPitching Speed: {\c&H5A78D1&}165km/h \N{\c&HE4EBEB&} Specialty: Throws fastballs,\Nbut can only throw\N straights and forkballs. \NPower Level: {\c&H5A78D1&}4 \N{\c&HE4EBEB&}ERA: {\c&H5A78D1&}5.23
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.49,0:17:18.05,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,And I will declare what kind \Nof pitch he will throw.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.59,0:17:20.56,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,#77 will now throw
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.26,0:17:23.56,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,a forkball straight down the middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.91,0:17:32.14,JoJo-Rumble,sfx,0000,0000,0000,,Rumbling
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.91,0:17:27.15,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,What?! He just declared his pitch?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.52,0:17:30.13,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,He will throw a forkball right down the middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.13,0:17:32.15,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Will you believe me or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.58,0:17:35.97,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Jotaro, he's just playing mind games with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.97,0:17:38.88,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let him declaring a pitch get to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.33,0:17:41.08,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,Throw, D'Arby.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.51,0:17:44.39,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Will you believe me or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.07,0:17:52.47,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Here it comes! It's coming \Nstraight down the middle!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.47,0:17:53.82,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,It's a straight!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.82,0:17:56.34,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,But is it going to remain a straight?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.82,0:17:59.09,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Will it fall or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.23,0:18:03.60,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,He swung! Jotaro bet on the forkball!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.83,0:18:07.06,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,But it's not falling! It's staying straight!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.23,0:18:10.52,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,He caught the bottom of the ball!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.52,0:18:13.48,JoJo-announcer,ump,0000,0000,0000,,Out!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.84,0:18:16.53,JoJo-announcer,game,0000,0000,0000,,Top of the first, three outs! Change!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.53,0:18:19.53,Inning 2,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Top of the 1st
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.54,0:18:22.40,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,How could you be so stupid?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.40,0:18:24.89,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,You actually believed him
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.89,0:18:27.46,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,and swung for a forkball!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.93,0:18:29.89,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.37,0:18:34.18,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,He was certain that I would swing for a forkball,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.74,0:18:36.60,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,so he changed it to a straight fastball.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.16,0:18:41.72,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,As he said, ever since we entered\Nthis mansion, I've been uncertain.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.24,0:18:47.39,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,He somehow knew that Star Platinum \Nwould throw a right punch.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.89,0:18:52.20,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,I-Impossible! So are you telling me
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.57,0:18:55.75,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,that he's reading your mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.13,0:18:59.45,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Next is the bottom of the first.\NIt's my turn on offense.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.25,0:19:11.54,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,This is a declaration that I will hit a home run.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.87,0:19:15.70,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,I shall hit the ball you throw into the left stands.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.98,0:19:20.51,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,Old man. You're certain that the game
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.51,0:19:22.48,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,and console aren't rigged in any way, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.48,0:19:24.44,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,There's no chance of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.44,0:19:28.18,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,And I've been keeping my eye \Nout for any kind of cheating.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.59,0:19:31.27,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,That means the secret lies with his Stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.27,0:19:32.94,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't just take souls.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.33,0:19:35.48,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,It has some kind of secret power.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.76,0:19:39.49,JoJo-internal/narrator,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,The course of action I'll take is...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.04,0:19:45.30,JoJo-internal/narrator,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,This should tell me something.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.71,0:19:49.75,JoJo-internal/narrator,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,What?! He's going to try to \Nhit the batter on purpose?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.15,0:19:53.88,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Where might you be aiming to throw? Inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.32,0:19:55.69,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Will it be high?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.16,0:19:57.37,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Or low?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.83,0:20:00.75,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Are you planning some sort of trick?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.11,0:20:13.69,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,What?! He dodged at the same\Ntime as the pitch was thrown!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.88,0:20:17.23,JoJo-Bazoon,sfx,0000,0000,0000,,Bazoom
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.34,0:20:21.90,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,H-He read that! He perfectly read it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.29,0:20:27.49,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way he could have done \Nthat without reading Jotaro's mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.49,0:20:28.79,JoJo-announcer,game,0000,0000,0000,,Home run!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.92,0:20:33.29,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,That's one run.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.61,0:20:35.23,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,I-Impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.67,0:20:38.11,JoJo-internal/narrator,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,We've met all kinds up until now,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.11,0:20:40.65,JoJo-internal/narrator,,0000,0000,0000,,but we've never seen a \NStand that could read minds.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.65,0:20:44.24,JoJo-internal/narrator,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,If it can read minds, then will no \Namount of intelligence or power
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.24,0:20:46.73,JoJo-internal/narrator,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,s-stand any chance against it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.20,0:20:49.81,JoJo-internal/narrator,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What are you going to do, Jotaro?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.25,0:21:02.32,Inning,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Bottom of the 1st
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.59,0:21:02.32,JoJo-Bam2,sfx,0000,0000,0000,,Bam
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.50,0:21:06.07,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it! H-He's declaring another home run.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.57,0:21:09.33,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Will the next one be outside?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.74,0:21:12.66,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,And low?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.66,0:21:14.90,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Or will it be a straight?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.65,0:21:26.22,JoJo-Bazoon,sfx,0000,0000,0000,,Clang
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.68,0:21:28.04,JoJo-announcer,game,0000,0000,0000,,Home run!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.58,0:21:30.10,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Four to two.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.05,0:21:37.19,JoJo-internal/narrator,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,By analyzing various data \Nand the situation you're in,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.19,0:21:39.58,JoJo-internal/narrator,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,you can figure out how an \Nopponent's mind works, to an extent.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.58,0:21:45.99,JoJo-internal/narrator,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,But this Stand can anticipate the \Nball's course with perfect precision.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.99,0:21:47.53,JoJo-internal/narrator,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,And he's not cheating!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.68,0:21:52.47,JoJo-internal/narrator,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Another home run! It's four to three!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.87,0:21:56.21,JoJo-internal/narrator,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,How can we stop him from reading our minds?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.21,0:21:57.55,JoJo-internal/narrator,,0000,0000,0000,,How?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.41,0:22:02.94,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to turn this around soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.94,0:22:05.26,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Now, will the next one be inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.26,0:22:08.47,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Down the middle? High? A changeup?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.47,0:22:09.81,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder where it'll go.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.44,0:22:15.81,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Your hat...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.81,0:22:17.51,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Heh, you fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.51,0:22:21.32,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think I'm using underhanded \Nmethods, like my brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.56,0:22:23.26,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Jotaro, that's not it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.26,0:22:25.07,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Hiding behind your hat won't help.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.47,0:22:29.32,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,He's not reading the reflection \Nof the screen in your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.64,0:22:32.73,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,And it's not a trick where \Nhe's listening to your fingers
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.73,0:22:35.58,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,as they push the buttons to figure \Nout what you're going to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.01,0:22:40.48,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,I've been watching him. \NThat's not what's going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.48,0:22:43.03,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,This is the first time I've \Nsweat or bled in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.03,0:22:44.12,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I took it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.66,0:22:47.38,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like you to hurry up \Nand throw your next pitch.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.71,0:22:51.82,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't think I have to \Nworry about sweating anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.82,0:22:53.39,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to declare my pitch.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.63,0:22:57.14,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,It's going to be a straight, \Nhigh to the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.46,0:22:58.85,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.85,0:23:01.90,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What? What did you just say, Jotaro?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.90,0:23:03.52,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,You heard me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.13,0:23:18.11,JoJo-Menacing,sfx,0000,0000,0000,,Menacing
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.79,0:23:06.42,JoJo-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you so old that your \Nhearing's gone, old man?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.42,0:23:08.86,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,I said I was going to declare my pitch.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.19,0:23:11.91,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,I'll throw a straight, high to the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.59,0:23:18.12,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,Jotaro!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.58,0:23:32.34,JoJo-Menacing,sfx,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,972)}Menacing
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.67,0:23:25.33,JoJo-main,jotaro,0000,0000,0000,,Will you believe me or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.09,0:23:29.57,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Are you stupid?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.01,0:23:36.93,JoJo-Preview,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Next Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.91,0:23:37.89,JoJo-main,joseph,0000,0000,0000,,What did you just say, Jotaro?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.89,0:23:39.94,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,I said I was going to declare my pitch.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.94,0:23:41.92,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Jotaro is not lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.92,0:23:42.41,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.41,0:23:43.93,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,You rigged the console somehow!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.93,0:23:44.44,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.44,0:23:46.82,JoJo-main,ter,0000,0000,0000,,Your school hat proves that you're cheating!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.82,0:23:49.99,JoJo-main,jojo,0000,0000,0000,,It's not cheating if you don't get caught.
